Meow. Meow.

11:47.457 --> 11:50.460
- Excuse me.
Where's the international aisle?

11:50.544 --> 11:51.962
Next one over?

11:52.045 --> 11:53.172
You work here, right?

11:53.255 --> 11:54.631
Yeah.

11:54.715 --> 11:56.884
- ASTRID: Yeah. Some people
are just vest people.

11:58.260 --> 12:03.182
Uh, so do they have
ground dhaniya, cori--cilantro?

12:03.265 --> 12:05.142
Damn it. Is it all over there?

12:05.225 --> 12:07.394
All spices
are in the international aisle,

12:07.477 --> 12:09.146
except for these.

12:09.229 --> 12:11.607
- ASTRID: Salt, pepper,
and everything

12:11.690 --> 12:13.358
bagel seasoning.
Yup. That tracks.

12:16.195 --> 12:18.113
All right, Kitty.
Let's travel abroad.

12:27.331 --> 12:28.624
- Hey.
- Hi.

12:28.707 --> 12:30.375
- I thought you were going
to an Indian grocery store?

12:30.459 --> 12:32.252
- Yeah, I did.
- Well,

12:32.336 --> 12:34.963
- but this is from Gero's.
- Uh, doy, James?

12:35.047 --> 12:37.341
I got this stuff from Gero's
because we're a Gero's family.

12:37.424 --> 12:38.550
- Hey.
I thought we talked about this.

12:38.634 --> 12:39.593
The doys are for others.

12:41.053 --> 12:43.347
- Where's Viv?
- She's using the litter box.

12:43.430 --> 12:46.350
- You know,
I am respecting her commitment.

12:46.433 --> 12:48.101
- I know.
- Well, well, how do we--

12:48.185 --> 12:49.561
what can--how can I help?
Where--what--how I--

12:49.645 --> 12:50.854
I don't know.

12:50.938 --> 12:52.940
I think what I'll do
is just access

12:53.023 --> 12:55.025
the deep well of information
from my ancestors

12:55.108 --> 12:56.360
from around the world.

12:57.444 --> 12:59.613
- Google. I see.
- Google.

12:59.696 --> 13:01.740
- You know what?
I hear is an excellent resource.

13:01.823 --> 13:03.367
Delicious Corey's kitchen.

13:03.450 --> 13:05.285
- Let's do that. Yeah.
- Uh-huh.

13:07.246 --> 13:08.497
<i>Today, me and daddy</i>

13:08.580 --> 13:11.625
<i>are gonna make</i>
<i>authentic Indian aloo gobi.</i>

13:11.708 --> 13:13.418
- Namaste,<i> Corey.</i>
- Namaste,<i> Daddy.</i>

13:13.502 --> 13:15.254
- I hate it. No.
- Sorry. So sorry. My bad.

13:15.337 --> 13:16.421
- I think
I'm just gonna wing it.

13:16.505 --> 13:18.048
- Yeah.
- Me, Viv,

13:18.131 --> 13:20.342
our Indian instincts
making chana bhaturas.

13:20.425 --> 13:22.052
- And I'm gonna follow
my instincts

13:22.135 --> 13:24.012
by having the phone tell me
the directions to Felix's game.

13:24.096 --> 13:25.722
- I believe in you.
- Nah you.

13:29.935 --> 13:31.520
- NISHA:<i> Hello?</i>
- Hi, Mom.

13:35.774 --> 13:38.151
Okay. Let's do this!

13:40.320 --> 13:41.363
Time to go, pal.
What's happening?

13:41.446 --> 13:43.198
You in the zone?

13:43.282 --> 13:45.576
- Am I distracting you?
- My toes are itchy.

13:45.659 --> 13:47.786
- Okay. I think that's
a solvable problem.

13:47.870 --> 13:49.246
Let's get out there
and scratch them toes.

13:52.875 --> 13:54.293
You sure that's all
that's bothering you, buddy?

13:54.376 --> 13:57.087
- I just don't feel
like playing, Dad.

13:57.171 --> 13:59.548
- Okay. Okay.
I understand that. I do.

13:59.631 --> 14:01.175
But perseverance
is also important

14:01.258 --> 14:02.509
and we've never
beaten Blue before,

14:02.593 --> 14:03.594
and they're very smug.

14:03.677 --> 14:07.222
So I just wanna
make sure that you're sure.

14:08.307 --> 14:09.349
Are you mad?

14:09.433 --> 14:11.852
No, no. Son, no.

14:13.228 --> 14:14.646
I just want you to find
something that you love,

14:14.730 --> 14:16.064
doesn't have to be baseball.

14:16.148 --> 14:18.192
Could be dancing.

14:18.275 --> 14:19.443
I wanna drive a tank.

14:21.486 --> 14:23.530
- Okay. I'll see
if there are lessons for that.

14:23.614 --> 14:25.115
- Let's just go home.
- Okay.

14:25.199 --> 14:26.909
- Okay. I gotta just
quickly tell your coach

14:26.992 --> 14:28.619
- that we're not coming.
- Hey, guys.

14:28.702 --> 14:30.954
We're gonna beat Blue today.
I can feel it.

14:31.038 --> 14:32.164
My guy.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.376
- You know,
let's just go straight home.

14:38.337 --> 14:41.423
- Okay. The base of all good
Indian cooking is the masala.

14:41.507 --> 14:43.091
Great. What is in that?

14:43.175 --> 14:45.594
Tomatoes, onion, jeera.

14:45.677 --> 14:47.554
- As far as quantity
is concerned,

14:47.638 --> 14:50.098
I know we're using
our instincts and my instinct

14:50.182 --> 14:53.685
is telling me a quarter
teaspoon of ground jeera.

14:53.769 --> 14:56.146
Half a teaspoon. One spoon.
Give me a clue, woman.

14:56.230 --> 14:58.065
- I'm half-Indian.

14:58.148 --> 14:59.316
You don't say.

14:59.399 --> 15:00.943
Okay then, half.

15:01.026 --> 15:03.529
- That's very cute.
She's actually a quarter.

15:03.612 --> 15:05.113
So is it actually a quarter?

15:05.197 --> 15:06.698
- Dawn, I need you
to chop more ginger.

15:06.782 --> 15:07.699
DAWN: On it.

15:07.783 --> 15:09.451
So exciting.

15:09.535 --> 15:12.913
Do I smell a crossover
with Delicious Corey's Kitchen.

15:12.996 --> 15:14.206
- Looking good,<i> bitoo.</i>
- ASTRID: Mom, Mom.

15:14.289 --> 15:16.667
- You gotta wait for me.
- Chulas wait for no one.

15:16.750 --> 15:19.461
- Okay, Viv, what's next?
- Um, let's see.

15:20.796 --> 15:21.880
These.

15:21.964 --> 15:24.383
- What is that?
- Chilies, and garam masala.

15:24.466 --> 15:26.134
- DAWN: Bo makes
some spicy mango cocktail

15:26.218 --> 15:28.345
- with garam masala.
- Oh, that sounds horrible.

15:28.428 --> 15:29.596
- It's not great.
- ASTRID: But hold on,

15:29.680 --> 15:31.723
can we just--because I--Mom,
I need to know the amounts

15:31.807 --> 15:32.766
and you're going too fast.

15:32.850 --> 15:34.601
Can I put these in?

15:34.685 --> 15:36.520
- NISHA: Yup. Go ahead,<i> bitoo.</i>
- ASTRID: You don't--Mom,

15:36.603 --> 15:38.105
this whole thing
would be a lot easier

15:38.188 --> 15:39.898
if you bothered to teach us
when we were kids.

15:39.982 --> 15:43.360
- Wow. I'm glad I'm the one
holding the knife. [groans]

15:43.443 --> 15:46.196
- VIV: I want to put
Rice Krispies in.

15:46.280 --> 15:48.031
- Viv, we gotta
follow the recipe,

15:48.115 --> 15:49.658
- whatever the hell that is.
- But to be fair,

15:49.741 --> 15:52.244
- she did try to teach us.
- No, she didn't.

15:52.327 --> 15:55.414
- Yes, I did, but you girls
never wanted to learn.

15:55.497 --> 15:57.499
Every time I said
we were having Indian food,

15:57.583 --> 15:59.251
there'd be
such moans and groans.

15:59.334 --> 16:01.461
You said you wanted hotdogs
and macaroni and cheese

16:01.545 --> 16:03.046
- like your friends.
- Not all of the time.

16:03.130 --> 16:04.965
- When are we making
Krispie Treats?

16:05.048 --> 16:06.091
- Wait. Viv, not now.
- No, no, no.

16:06.175 --> 16:08.010
We would have
Indian food once a week,

16:08.093 --> 16:09.761
but you were embarrassed
of the smells

16:09.845 --> 16:11.263
and the yellow fingernails,

16:11.346 --> 16:13.599
and said you wanted
to eat normal food.

16:13.682 --> 16:15.434
So, one day I just stopped.

16:17.811 --> 16:19.813
- Viv, Viv, Viv. No.
Don't, Viv...

16:31.325 --> 16:33.702
- NISHA: Leave it.
We can start over.

16:33.785 --> 16:35.454
ASTRID: Let's just forget it.

16:35.537 --> 16:37.998
It's not like Viv is gonna eat
the chanas anyway.

16:38.081 --> 16:39.583
Why would she?

16:39.666 --> 16:42.127
Most Indian thing
we have is chai.

16:42.211 --> 16:44.379
- It's from Starbucks.
- It's not a big deal.

16:44.463 --> 16:45.839
Maybe not for you, Mom.

16:45.923 --> 16:48.008
You go out in the world
and people know who you are.

16:48.091 --> 16:49.635
Those people at the Indian store

16:49.718 --> 16:51.220
did not even know
that I was Indian.

16:51.303 --> 16:53.180
And they did think
that I was racist.

16:53.263 --> 16:55.474
- Calling them
those people doesn't help.

16:58.769 --> 17:01.480
I get called exotic.

17:01.563 --> 17:03.607
Which means pretty
but not quite why.

17:03.690 --> 17:05.526
- Well, that describes me
to a T.

17:05.609 --> 17:07.736
- You think
I don't have to prove myself,

17:07.819 --> 17:10.364
a brown woman
in the Western world?

17:10.447 --> 17:14.451
<i>Beta, </i>who cares
about everybody else?

17:14.535 --> 17:17.913
I know exactly who you are,
my daughter,

17:17.996 --> 17:21.166
strong, independent,

17:21.250 --> 17:23.085
unable to cook in two cultures.

17:23.168 --> 17:26.213
- Well, I burnt pad thai,
so, make that three.

17:30.342 --> 17:33.470
Excuse me.
I gotta go apologize to a cat.

17:36.974 --> 17:38.183
Hey, Viv.

17:45.023 --> 17:47.234
Meow. Meow, meow.

17:49.278 --> 17:50.988
Well, I guess Viv left.

17:51.071 --> 17:53.574
Oh, well, at least I get
to keep all her toys.

17:53.657 --> 17:56.118
No, you can't. I'm right here.

17:56.201 --> 17:58.620
- There you are.
- I'm sorry I messed up.

17:58.704 --> 18:00.664
Hey, you didn't.

18:00.747 --> 18:02.583
I'm the one
who made a mess of things.

18:05.419 --> 18:07.171
Rice Krispie Treat?

18:07.254 --> 18:10.966
- I know these aren't Indian
but I really like them.

18:11.049 --> 18:12.968
- You know,
my dad used to make these

18:13.051 --> 18:14.219
for me when I was little.

18:14.303 --> 18:16.889
- Was he Indian?
Can dads be Indian?

18:16.972 --> 18:19.808
- My dad wasn't Indian,
but--but some dads are,

18:19.892 --> 18:21.435
like, half a billion of them.

18:21.518 --> 18:23.562
They're my favorite.

18:23.645 --> 18:25.647
Mine too.

18:25.731 --> 18:27.482
When I used
to make them with my dad,

18:27.566 --> 18:29.359
he would let me mix
in all the marshmallows

18:29.443 --> 18:31.778
and sometimes we'd throw in
some special treats

18:31.862 --> 18:33.655
like chocolate chips
or licorice all sorts,

18:33.739 --> 18:35.115
which are disgusting.

18:35.199 --> 18:37.993
But the rainbow sprinkles, woo!

18:38.076 --> 18:39.828
Can we put cookies in?

18:39.912 --> 18:41.330
- We can throw
whole chocolate bars in.

18:41.413 --> 18:42.998
Yes.

18:43.081 --> 18:45.000
- You know how I told you
that you were English,

18:45.083 --> 18:47.252
- and Scottish, and Indian?
- Uh-hmm.

18:47.336 --> 18:49.755
- Well, you are
all those things.

18:49.838 --> 18:51.965
But I forgot to tell you
that you are something

18:52.049 --> 18:53.550
that's totally
different than me,

18:53.634 --> 18:54.843
or Daddy, or Nanima.

18:54.927 --> 18:56.386
You're you.

18:57.596 --> 19:01.141
And there's nobody
on planet Earth who is like you.

19:01.225 --> 19:03.644
<i>Becoming a parent</i>
<i>is a massive shift in identity.</i>

19:03.727 --> 19:05.771
You can't escape
the tickle monster!

19:06.813 --> 19:10.275
<i>Your name changes to mom</i>
<i>or dad like almost overnight.</i>

19:10.359 --> 19:14.655
Viv, I blamed your dad
for eating these.

19:14.738 --> 19:16.532
- JAMES:<i> Your life turns</i>
<i>into talking about your kids,</i>

19:16.615 --> 19:18.700
<i>following them around,</i>
<i>collecting pictures of them.</i>

19:18.784 --> 19:20.536
- ASTRID:<i> It's like being</i>
<i>obsessed with a K-pop group.</i>

19:20.619 --> 19:22.829
- JAMES:<i> Yeah, it sucks</i>
<i>to lose some of your identity.</i>

19:22.913 --> 19:24.289
- ASTRID:
<i>But it's amazing to watch</i>

19:24.373 --> 19:25.832
<i>your kids develop theirs.</i>

19:25.916 --> 19:27.876
- What are you doing?
- Well, I'm busting a move.

19:27.960 --> 19:29.044
What does
it look like I'm doing?

19:29.127 --> 19:31.755
- Stop, Daddy.
- What? I can't--I can't stop.

19:31.839 --> 19:34.550
- What--what's happening?
- You have to pop your hip.

19:34.633 --> 19:36.301
- I have to the pop my hip?
How do I do that, like that?

19:36.385 --> 19:38.011
- You're doing great.
- Thanks, buddy.

19:38.095 --> 19:39.263
Now, shimmy.

19:42.266 --> 19:44.685
- ASTRID: Why are you limping?
- I shimmied too hard.

19:44.768 --> 19:46.603
- So are we ordering
pizza or what?

19:46.687 --> 19:48.605
DAWN: No need.<i> Voila!</i>

19:48.689 --> 19:50.816
- I added a little of this,
a little of that.

19:50.899 --> 19:54.069
It's not what we were going for
but it's pretty good.

19:54.152 --> 19:55.487
And it smells delicious.

19:55.571 --> 19:56.989
- The secrets
the Rice Krispies.

19:57.072 --> 19:58.866
I want one.

19:58.949 --> 20:00.742
- What is--this is amazing.
What do you call it?

20:00.826 --> 20:02.911
- I call them
hot sloppy Nishas.

20:04.955 --> 20:07.791
All right,<i> jaldee,</i>
let's eat before it gets cold.

20:07.875 --> 20:09.001
[snarls]

20:09.084 --> 20:10.127
[chuckles]

20:11.211 --> 20:14.006
- Hi, and welcome
to<i> Delicious Corey's Kitchen.</i>

20:14.089 --> 20:17.134
Today, I'm gonna show you
how to make pumpkin gnocchi

20:17.217 --> 20:20.470
with whipped ricotta
and burnt butter cashews,

20:20.554 --> 20:23.056
alongside
with my sous-chef, Mom.

20:24.474 --> 20:27.561
- That's right,
Delicious Corey.

20:27.644 --> 20:31.106
There ain't nothing hokey
about this gnocchi.

20:31.190 --> 20:33.525
Um, I couldn't find
any ethically sourced cashews,

20:33.609 --> 20:35.444
so I had to substitute walnuts.

20:39.239 --> 20:40.908
I'm gonna need a minute.

20:40.991 --> 20:43.452
It's okay.
I'm just gonna inhale, exhale...

20:43.535 --> 20:45.662
Um, we'll be right back.

20:45.746 --> 20:47.581
Bo. Bo, come quick.

20:47.664 --> 20:49.917
Corey is freaking out.
